South African Equity Market Preview: Adcorp, Business Connexion, Grindrod

-- B y   L a u r e n   v a n   d e r   W e s t h u i z e n
-- 
2011-05-24T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/south-african-stock-preview-adcorp-nampak-pinnacle-point.html
The following stocks may rise or fall
in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index climbed 386.52, or 1.2
percent, to 31,731.05 at the 5 p.m. close in Johannesburg.  Adcorp Holdings Ltd. (ADR)  : The investment company
releases full-year earnings. The stock remained unchanged at
27.30 rand.  ArcelorMittal South Africa Ltd. (ACL)  : Africa’s largest
steelmaker holds its annual general meeting at 11 a.m. The
shares increased 65 cents, or 0.8 percent, to 78.90 rand.  Business Connexion Group Ltd. (BCX)  : The information and
communications technology company will sell its 70 percent stake
in Destiny E-Commerce to Verifone Singapore PTE Ltd. for 255
million rand ($36 million). The stock gained 2 cents, or 0.4
percent, to 4.88 rand.  Grindrod Ltd. (GND)  : Africa’s biggest shipping company
holds its annual general meeting at 2 p.m. The shares retreated
34 cents, or 2.5 percent, to 13.15 rand.  Nampak Ltd. (NPK)  : The packaging company releases first-
half earnings. The shares rose 15 cents, or 0.7 percent, to
21.50 rand.  Pinnacle Point Group Ltd. (PNG)  : The property and golf-
resorts developer has received two separate offers to buy its
Lagos development as well as an offer to acquire the Wedgewood
development. The stock was unchanged at 1 cent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lauren van der Westhuizen at  at
 lvanderwesth@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
